[The dates that the 3 individuals became ill with yellow fever (YF), with the deaths of 2, are not given, but the fatalities may have occurred on or shortly before the announcement of YF confirmation. The park closures and vaccination campaigns in these areas of risk are urgent, since the virus continues to circulate in the forested areas. Brazil-wide, the WHO reported 779 confirmed cases and 262 deaths, a few more than stated above (see Yellow fever - Americas (66): PAHO/WHO 20171214.5504146). So far, none of these cases has been attributed to the urban _Aedes aegypti_ transmission cycle. All have been reported due to the sylvan (forest) cycle with related monkey deaths. The preventive measures are essential to prevent the virus reaching urban and suburban areas where _Aedes aegypti_ are abundant. The situation in Brazil illustrates the need to maintain routine YF vaccination in endemic YF areas in order to avoid health emergencies. - Mod.TY

